

= Economist Roles at Brokerage Firms

== Overview

Economists at brokerage firms provide macroeconomic analysis, forecasting, and market commentary that supports trading, sales, and client advisory activities. In Australia, major brokers like Morgans Financial, Bell Potter, Ord Minnett, and international firms like UBS and Macquarie maintain economics teams that produce research on domestic and global economic trends, monetary policy, fiscal developments, and their implications for financial markets.

Unlike academic or government economists who focus on policy design or theoretical research, brokerage economists translate economic developments into actionable investment insights for institutional and retail clients. Their work directly influences trading strategies, client positioning, and investment recommendations across asset classes.

This document outlines economist roles at Australian brokerage firms, from junior economists supporting research production through to chief economists setting the firm's macroeconomic view and representing the organisation externally.

